helped launch and advised hotwirecom intralinks which was cofounded by his brother arthur and inphonic buycom and peoplepc—each of which became billion dollar market cap public companies in the scitation needed sculley went political in the early s on behalf of republican tom campbell who in  was running in the california republican primary to be the party candidate for a united states senate seat sculley hosted a fundraiser for campbell at his ranch in woodside sculley had become acquainted with hillary clinton serving with her on a national education council when bill clinton ran for president sculley supported him sculley sat next to hillary clinton during the presidents first state of the union address in january  in  sculley became the chairman of live picture a californiabased company to oversee its push into highquality lowbandwidth imaging over the internet usm in venture capital was provided for the company sculley later left the company but remained an investor in  live picture filed for federal bankruptcy protection as part of a plan to be acquired by mgi software in  sculley cofounded poptech with bob metcalfe and several other dignitaries from the technology industry in  he joined the board of directors of buycomp llc now buycom an internetonly computer store two years later he partnered with dennis m lynch to launch signature providing marketing services to small to mediumsized businesses in  sculley and lynch transitioned the company into a learning program for rising entrepreneurs months later lynch left the company while sculley continued to consult and work with small businesses including inphonic whose board of directors he later joined inphonic is an online retailer of cell phones and wireless plans sculleys early leadership helped steer inphonic towards its successful ipo in  sculley served as the vice chairman of the inphonic board of directors inphonic filed for chapter  in  in  sculley endorsed and invested in the wine clip a wine accessory product which claims to accelerate the aeration of wine by exposure to magnets a year later he helped in the founding of verified person inc an online preemployment screening company he currentlywhen serves on the board of directors in  sculley joined the board of directors at openpeak a maker of software for wireless consumer electronics digital media computers and home systems in the same year sculley became a venture partner at rho ventures in march  sculley was named chairman of identrust formerly digital signature trust company a san franciscobased firm focusing on verifying identity and boosting financial security before speaking at the silicon valley  conference sculley was interviewed by cnet in october  where he explained the mistakes he made at apple concerning the apple newton and hypercard sculley cancelled apples first handheld mobile tablet penmac led by paul mercer with applications by samir arora and instead signed an agreement to work with sharp electronics on the newton technology also in  sculley was interviewed by the bbc for the television documentary the worlds most powerful episode steve jobs vs bill gates discussing his time at apple during the s as ceo in  he was interviewed for cult of mac on the topics of steve jobs and design sculley has spoken at poptech since its opening in  every year except for dead link in  sculley cofounded the data company zeta global with business partner david a steinberg and in january  the data analytics firm xl marketing rebranded and incorporated its resources into zeta interactive relaunching it as a big datadriven marketing firm on january   sculley was a panelist at a forum organized by zeta which featured ad executives marketers and nfl executive to discuss the changes in the way companies market and reach consumers since sculleys time at apple in  when the computer company featured what became one of the first iconic super bowl ads—the  commercial in october  zeta interactive was again rebranded as zeta global in  sculley cofounded obi mobiles a smartphone brand aimed at the emerging markets the company was renamed obi worldphone he has also been working in the health care industry focusing on rxadvance a cloudbased platform that helps pharmaceutical companies hospitals and insurers manage chronically ill patients living at home personal lifeedit sculley married ruth stepdaughter of pepsico president donald kendall in  with whom he had two children the couple divorced in  in  he married carol lee adams exwife of a former pepsico vice president ultimately divorcing in  in  adams filed a lawsuit alleging that sculley did not disclose over  million in assets during their divorce proceedings a spokesman for sculley denied the allegations sculley married diane gibbs poli vice president and design coordinator for wittman building corporation in  and they live in palm beach florida referencesedit  beverage industry  google books booksgoogleca  retrieved on   malone infinite loop pg   the new york times company news – visionary apple chairman moves on archived  at the wayback machine  the new york times new strategy set by apple archived  at the wayback machine  sculley quic bio at end of article macrumors  retrieved    isaacson walter  steve jobs new york ny simon  schuster p  isbn    january  zeta interactive retrieved    archived copy archived from the original on  retrieved    archived copy archived from the original on  retrieved    archived copy archived from the original on  retrieved    httpswwwnytimescomdeathshtmlrpermanent dead link  profile archived april   at the wayback machine lowendmaccom accessed january    wharton – leadership across industries hightech john sculley whartonupennedu retrieved    sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg   sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg –  sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg   sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg –  sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg   sculley odyssey pepsi to apple pg –  michael s malone infinite loop new york doubleda