onals john has served as national trial counsel on birth and catastrophic injury litigation for numerous hospital systems and insurance carriers and as national coordinating counsel for one of the nation’s largest health care organizations over the past  years john has developed a diverse civil trial practice involving an array of industries including health care insurance real estate construction oil and gas financial and pharmaceuticals he has represented a variety of clients ranging from fortune  companies to governmental entities in complex commercial litigation personal injury lawsuits class actions administrative proceedings and investigations john has tried and managed lawsuits in state and federal courts throughout texas and numerous other states john and his wife karen have three children  while john has always been a sports fanatic his support of his childrens activities led to his passionate involvement in coaching youth sports john served as head football coach of the parish episcopal thth grade team for many years and as assistant football coach of the schools high school team since  john also serves on parishs board of trustees and served as chair of the board of visitors for his undergraduate alma mater depauw university   admitted texas  oklahoma  montana  us supreme court  us court of appeals th circuit  us district court eastern district of texas  us district court northern district of texas  us district court southern district of texas  us district court western district of texas  us district court eastern district of oklahoma    education jd southern methodist university school of law  ba depauw university    honors board certified in civil trial law by the texas board of legal specialization board certified in personal injury trial law by the board of legal specialization board certified by the american board of professional liability attorneys elected to the american board of trial advocates “abota” selected to d magazines best lawyers in dalla